Sudan condemned the American attacks on its embassy in Khartoum, pulling down the flag in protest.
Many citizens criticized the retaliation for the bombings in Nairobi and Dar.
President Clinton's actions were seen as deflecting attention from his own scandals.
Sudan sought a UN investigation into the alleged pharmaceutical plant hit by US missiles.
Despite American claims of chemical weapons production, Sudan insisted it was a legitimate pharmaceutical facility.
The attack coincided with strikes on Bin Laden's bases, raising suspicions of Sudan's involvement.
Sudanese security forces guarded the site, denying any ties to terrorism.
